By Onyebuchi Ezigbo Nigeria recorded 1,883 new confirmed cases of Covid-19 on Saturday. According to the daily statistics report by the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC), 1,883 new confirmed cases and one death was recorded in Nigeria. The report posted on NCDC website said that till date, 130,557 cases have been confirmed, while 103,712 cases have been discharged and 1,578 deaths recorded in 36 states and the Federal Capital Territory (FCT). The 1,883 new cases are reported from 23 states â€” Lagos (1040), FCT (298), Anambra (86), Rivers (54), Taraba (45), Ogun (42), Oyo (40), Akwa Ibom (38), Sokoto (30), Ebonyi (30), Imo (28), Kaduna (28), Osun (27), Kano (21), Benue (19), Edo (17), Gombe (15), Ekiti (9), Delta (8), Jigawa (3), Kwara (2), Bayelsa (2) and Plateau (1).